<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><entry xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xml:id="entry_bælon" xml:lang="os"><form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>bælon</orth></form><form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>bæIæw</orth></form><sense><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>голубь домашний</q></cit><note type="comment" xml:lang="">; </note><note type="comment" xml:lang="">; </note><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>domestic pigeon</q></cit><note type="comment" xml:lang="">; </note><note type="comment" xml:lang="">; </note></sense><cit type="exampleGroup" corresp="#sense_bælon." n=""><cit type="example"><quote>wælarvæj ratæxʒæn ærtæ bælony</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>с неба прилетят три голубя</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>three pigeons will fly from the sky</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_ЮОПам."/><biblScope>III 137</biblScope></bibl></cit><cit type="example"><quote>smax — dywwæ ænæaīpp bælony</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>вы — два непорочных голубя</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>you are two immaculate pigeons</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_Сека"/><biblScope>38</biblScope></bibl></cit><cit type="example" xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg type="dialect"><lang/></usg><quote>æ duwwæ usqebæl duwwæors bælæwi</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>на двух его плечах два белых голубя</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>there are two white pigeons on his two shoulders</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_СОПам."/><biblScope>II 99</biblScope></bibl></cit><cit type="example" xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg type="dialect"><lang/></usg><quote>zumægon cʼewtæ æncæ: ... bælæw, ʒæǧinʒæg, sunt...</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>зимние птицы суть: голубь, сорока, ворон…</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>winter birds are the following: pigeon, magpie, crow</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_FS"/><biblScope>I 19</biblScope></bibl></cit></cit><cit type="exampleGroup" corresp="#sense_." n=""><cit type="example"><quote>wælarvæj ratæxʒæn ærtæ bælony</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>с неба прилетят три голубя</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>three pigeons will fly from the sky</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_ЮОПам."/><biblScope>III 137</biblScope></bibl></cit><cit type="example"><quote>smax — dywwæ ænæaīpp bælony</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>вы — два непорочных голубя</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>you are two immaculate pigeons</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_Сека"/><biblScope>38</biblScope></bibl></cit><cit type="example" xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg type="dialect"><lang/></usg><quote>æ duwwæ usqebæl duwwæors bælæwi</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>на двух его плечах два белых голубя</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>there are two white pigeons on his two shoulders</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_СОПам."/><biblScope>II 99</biblScope></bibl></cit><cit type="example" xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg type="dialect"><lang/></usg><quote>zumægon cʼewtæ æncæ: ... bælæw, ʒæǧinʒæg, sunt...</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>зимние птицы суть: голубь, сорока, ворон…</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>winter birds are the following: pigeon, magpie, crow</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_FS"/><biblScope>I 19</biblScope></bibl></cit></cit><etym xml:lang="ru">По-видимому, индоевропейское слово, но мало распространенное. На иранской почве можно указать <mentioned xml:lang="zza"><lang/><w>baurā́n</w><gloss><q>голубь</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><ref target="#ref_KPF"/><biblScope>Abt. III, Bd. IV, стр. 212</biblScope></bibl>); за пределами иранского — <mentioned xml:lang="lt"><lang/><w>balañdis</w><gloss><q>голубь</q></gloss></mentioned>. Форма %ibælon%i (вместо ожидаемого %ibæron%i), а также конечное %i-æw%i в дигорском — вторичные явления. Исходное значение было, вероятно, ласкательное: ‘птенчик’, ‘птенец’, к <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/><w>bāla-</w><gloss><q>дитя</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w>bālaka-</w><gloss><q>ребенок</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/><gloss><q>детеныш животного</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="ru"><lang/><w>баловать</w></mentioned> и пр.; для семантики ср. <mentioned xml:lang="ru"><lang/><w>голубь</w></mentioned> и <mentioned xml:lang="ru"><lang/><w>голубить</w></mentioned>. Возможность развития значения ‘дитя’ → ‘голубь’ подтверждается <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/><w>bālāgra-</w><gloss><q>голубятня</q></gloss></mentioned> при <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/><w>bāla</w><gloss><q>дитя</q></gloss></mentioned>. Вряд ли к <mentioned xml:lang="ine"><lang/><w>*bhel-</w><gloss><q>белый</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><ref target="#ref_Hehn"/><biblScope>[[%b6%b]] 241</biblScope></bibl>).%n<bibl><ref target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"/><biblScope>II 108</biblScope></bibl>; <bibl><ref target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."/><biblScope>8</biblScope></bibl>.— <bibl><ref target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>50, 61</biblScope></bibl>.</etym><etym xml:lang="en">Appearingly, it is an Indo-European but less common word. The following words could be indicated as of Iranian origin: <mentioned xml:lang="zza"><lang/><w>baurā́n</w><gloss><q>pigeon</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><ref target="#ref_KPF"/><biblScope>Abt. III, Bd. IV, стр. 212</biblScope></bibl>); apart from Iranian — <mentioned xml:lang="lt"><lang/><w>balañdis</w><gloss><q>pigeon</q></gloss></mentioned>. The form %ibælon%i (instead of expected %ibæron%i) and the final %i-æw%i in Digor as well are secondary phenomena. The initial meaning probably was a pet name 'nestling', 'little nestling', to <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/><w>bāla-</w><gloss><q>infant</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w>bālaka-</w><gloss><q>child</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/><gloss><q>animal's cub</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="ru"><lang/><w>balovat'</w></mentioned> etc.; for the semantics cf. <mentioned xml:lang="ru"><lang/><w>golub'</w></mentioned> and <mentioned xml:lang="ru"><lang/><w>golubit'</w></mentioned>. The possibility of the development of the meaning 'child' → ‘pigeon’ is confirmed by <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/><w>bālāgra-</w><gloss><q>dovecote</q></gloss></mentioned> which is related to <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/><w>bāla</w><gloss><q>child</q></gloss></mentioned>. Unlikely to <mentioned xml:lang="ine"><lang/><w>*bhel-</w><gloss><q>white</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><ref target="#ref_Hehn"/><biblScope>%r6%r 241</biblScope></bibl>).%n<bibl><ref target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"/><biblScope>II 108</biblScope></bibl>; <bibl><ref target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."/><biblScope>8</biblScope></bibl>.— <bibl><ref target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>50, 61</biblScope></bibl>.</etym></entry>